<a name="1">[1]</a> <a href="#1" id=1>Dimensionality on Summarization.</a>
<a name="2">[2]</a> <a href="#2" id=2>A summarization system consisting of a multi-dimensional classification space of summary in form of semantic link network of pictures and language representations and a requirement space defined and managed by users.</a>
<a name="3">[3]</a> <a href="#3" id=3>e) Construct a semantic link network of pictures, tags and language representations in relevant texts as the summary.</a>
<a name="4">[4]</a> <a href="#4" id=4>The form of summary can be a semantic link network of texts, pictures, audios, and videos.</a>
<a name="5">[5]</a> <a href="#5" id=5>Summarization is involved in representation and understanding.</a>
<a name="6">[6]</a> <a href="#6" id=6>If we regard a text as a graph of words or sentences, text summarization can be regarded as a problem of summarizing a semantic link network [Zhuge, 2009], where nodes and edges can be texts, pictures and videos.</a>
<a name="7">[7]</a> <a href="#7" id=7>Text summarization is a special case of summarization.</a>
<a name="8">[8]</a> <a href="#8" id=8>summary should use the core representations in the original representation.</a>
<a name="9">[9]</a> <a href="#9" id=9>The core representations in one representation (e.g.,, text) render its topic.</a>
<a name="10">[10]</a> <a href="#10" id=10>The core representation renders the core idea of a representation.</a>
<a name="11">[11]</a> <a href="#11" id=11>Another way is to establish basic semantic links between pictures, find the best matched text, and make necessary text summarization.</a>
<a name="12">[12]</a> <a href="#12" id=12>Some summaries incorporate pictures, videos, graphs, or tables into texts.</a>
<a name="13">[13]</a> <a href="#13" id=13>A multi-dimensional classification space of summarization methods.</a>
<a name="14">[14]</a> <a href="#14" id=14>As a kind of language representation, summarization should be based on the basic principles of language use.</a>
<a name="15">[15]</a> <a href="#15" id=15>The intention of representation is indicated by core representations and by citation from other representations.</a>
<a name="16">[16]</a> <a href="#16" id=16>Discovering the semantic link networks that the pictures involved in can help automatic summarization.</a>
